/**
 * Lifecycle Output Protocol — Roundtrip Shape Assertions (#1794)
 *
 * WHAT THIS TEST DOES
 * -------------------
 * For every lifecycle hook event that does NOT consume hookEventName or
 * additionalContext (WorktreeCreate, WorktreeRemove, CwdChanged, FileChanged,
 * ConfigChange, InstructionsLoaded, TaskCreated, Notification), this test:
 *
 *   1. Fires a synthetic input through the handler directly.
 *   2. Asserts that result.hookSpecificOutput?.hookEventName is either
 *      undefined OR matches the firing event (never 'UserPromptSubmit').
 *   3. Asserts that result.hookSpecificOutput?.additionalContext is undefined.
 *
 * WHY TWO LAYERS MATTER
 * ---------------------
 * PR-1 (fix/m119.1794-worktree-output-shape) fixes the call-site in
 * worktree-lifecycle-logger.ts. This PR (dispatcher output guard) fixes the
 * structural asymmetry in the dispatcher. This test catches the bug regardless
 * of which layer prevents it — two independent fail-safes.
 *
 * HOW TO VERIFY THE TEST IS NOT VACUOUS
 * --------------------------------------
 * Without both the call-site fix (PR-1) and the dispatcher guard, the
 * WorktreeRemove test below fails because worktree-lifecycle-logger.ts
 * calls outputPromptContext() which stamps hookEventName:'UserPromptSubmit'.
 * The dispatcher guard strips it before CC reads stdout.
 *
 * Refs #1794
 */

